      "content": "The legal framework of a secular state must always take precedence over the doctrines of any single religious group. The foundational principle of a modern democracy is that all citizens are equal under the law, regardless of their beliefs. While religious freedom is a vital right, it cannot be used as a shield to violate fundamental civil rights or public safety mandates. Therefore, the state's duty to ensure equal treatment and public welfare must ultimately prevail.",
