    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait, so you're saying religious freedom is basically secondary to the state? that seems a bit extreme. if a person's core identity and connection to their god is at stake, isn't that just as fundamental as a civil right? aren't you essentially saying that the state's version of \"equality\" is more important than a person's sincere conscience?",
